<MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom=true>Frequently asked questions</MudText>

<MudGrid Spacing="5" Class="pa-2">
    <MudItem lg="6" sm="12" Class="faq">
        <FaqItem>
            <Question>How can I play on Android?</Question>
            <Answer>On an Android device, it is easiest to play using the Dragalipatch app by LukeFZ. This creates a modified app you can use to play Dawnshard by patching to <MudLink Href="https://dawnshard.co.uk" Typo="Typo.body2">https://dawnshard.co.uk</MudLink>.</Answer>
            <Action><MudButton Color="Color.Secondary" Href="https://github.com/LukeFZ/DragaliPatch/releases/latest">Download Dragalipatch</MudButton></Action>
        </FaqItem>
    </MudItem>  
    <MudItem lg="6" sm="12" Class="faq">
        <FaqItem>
            <Question>How can I play on iOS?</Question>
            <Answer>The iOS setup process is a little more involved -- please see the <code>#ios-setup-support</code> channel on the Discord server.</Answer>
            <Action><MudButton Color="Color.Secondary" Href="https://discord.gg/j9zSttjjWj">Join Discord</MudButton></Action>
        </FaqItem>
    </MudItem>  
    <MudItem lg="12" sm="12" Class="faq">
        <FaqItem>
            <Question>Do I have to start over?</Question>
            <Answer>You can start over, or you can create an account on the BaaS server, which is a replacement for the Nintendo account mechanism from the original game. You can attach a savefile to this and have that uploaded onto a server.</Answer>
            <Action><MudButton Color="Color.Secondary" Href="https://baas.lukefz.xyz/">Visit Baas.LukeFZ.xyz</MudButton></Action>
        </FaqItem>
    </MudItem>
</MudGrid>

